zations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"closed","commit_id":"b167d30420a2bda3dfd526d10eb97d803e6f6e3e","commit_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/commits/b167d30420a2bda3dfd526d10eb97d803e6f6e3e","created_at":"2019-02-12T12:27:32Z","state_reason":null,"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/comments/462740837","html_url":"https://github.com/rclone/rclone/issues/2966#issuecomment-462740837","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/2966","id":462740837,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ2Mjc0MDgzNw==","user":{"login":"ncw","id":536803,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzNjgwMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/536803?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw","html_url":"https://github.com/ncw","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2019-02-12T12:28:13Z","updated_at":"2019-02-12T12:28:13Z","body":"> I've tested that beta version on a Windows 10 Pro machine (64 bits), and the `--ca-cert` works like a charm.\r\n\r\nExcellent :-)\r\n\r\n> So, if it doens't break any rclone naming convention, would it be possible to rename that flag to `--cacert` instead? It would be easier to remember, I think.\r\n\r\nThat is a good suggestion and I try to stay compatible with other programs where possible.  On reflection I think I'd rather leave it how it is as rclone has rather a lot of ssl related options using the `thing`-`thing` convention so `--ca-cert` fits in better there.\r\n\r\nClient options\r\n\r\n      --ca-cert string         CA certificate used to verify servers\r\n      --client-cert string     Client SSL certificate (PEM) for mutual TLS auth\r\n      --client-key string      Client SSL private key (PEM) for mutual TLS auth\r\n\r\nSever options (eg `rclone serve http`)\r\n\r\n      --cert string            SSL PEM key (concatenation of certificate and CA certificate)\r\n      --client-ca string       Client certificate authority to verify clients with\r\n      --key string             SSL PEM Private key\r\n\r\nrc server options\r\n\r\n      --rc-cert string        SSL PEM key (concatenation of certificate and CA certificate)\r\n      --rc-client-ca string   Client certificate authority to verify clients with\r\n      --rc-key string         SSL PEM Private key\r\n\r\nI note also that wget uses `--ca-certificate` just to be similar but different!\r\n\r\nI thought the flag parsing library allowed aliases, but it doesn't alas!\r\n\r\nI've merged this to master now which means it will be in [the latest beta](https://beta.rclone.org) in 15-30 mins and released in v1.47","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/comments/462740837/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"ncw","id":536803,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzNjgwMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/536803?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw","html_url":"